item.title: Compile and cant connect to my server (error connecting to server)
item.dc:creator: @go_armand go armand
item.description:
@go_armand wrote:

make sure your server is online…
have you portfowarded correctly.
set up no-ip and have the no-ip duc running?
to check if your server is online, go to http://canyouseeme.org/
and type 43594 into the port box.
if your server is online it will say yes, we can see you or something…

then once you’re sure thats online.
go into your client.java file in your client folders.
then make sure everything is changed from the previous source to the ip that you just set up.
once you’re done in there. search the rest of your client files for the old ip and replace it with your new one.
save every file you eddited. <— make sure you have backup incase you mess something up.
compile.
restart both source and client and you should be all good.
